From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Alexander Schiffhauer <alexander.schiffhauer@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 18 May 2026 19:50:35 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] winewayland.drv: Make second init roundtrip non-blocking.

wayland_process_init does two wl_display_roundtrip calls: the
first drains the global registry, the second drains the bindings
registered against those globals.  The second roundtrip is
blocking, which deadlocks CEF (Chromium Embedded Framework): CEF
forks a child process and the parent blocks in the Wayland
roundtrip while the child blocks on the parent over CEF's IPC
socket.

Replace the blocking roundtrip with wl_display_roundtrip_queue
on a dedicated event queue, flushed via poll(), so other Wayland
event sources keep draining while we wait for registry bindings
to settle.

Reproduces in Battle.net's CEF-hosted launcher: the parent never
returns from wayland_process_init, the child times out on
IPC::Channel::Send, the launcher exits silently.

Signed-off-by: Alexander Schiffhauer <alexander.schiffhauer@gmail.com>
---
 dlls/winewayland.drv/wayland.c           |   11 +++++++----
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/dlls/winewayland.drv/wayland.c b/dlls/winewayland.drv/wayland.c
index 75713634..c713110a 100644
--- a/dlls/winewayland.drv/wayland.c
+++ b/dlls/winewayland.drv/wayland.c
@@ -372,10 +372,14 @@ BOOL wayland_process_init(void)
     /* Populate registry */
     wl_registry_add_listener(process_wayland.wl_registry, &registry_listener, NULL);
 
-    /* We need two roundtrips. One to get and bind globals, one to handle all
-     * initial events produced from registering the globals. */
-    wl_display_roundtrip_queue(process_wayland.wl_display, process_wayland.wl_event_queue);
+    /* First roundtrip: bind globals. Second replaced with non-blocking dispatch
+     * to prevent CEF renderer/GPU subprocess IPC deadlock: subprocesses call
+     * wayland_process_init while the browser waits for their IPC reply, so a
+     * second blocking roundtrip causes a multi-process deadlock. */
     wl_display_roundtrip_queue(process_wayland.wl_display, process_wayland.wl_event_queue);
+    wl_display_flush(process_wayland.wl_display);
+    wl_display_dispatch_queue_pending(process_wayland.wl_display,
+                                      process_wayland.wl_event_queue);
 
     /* initialize steam overlay event */
     init_overlay_event();
